5:
Damn... There's a lot of them. So the
rumors about the Defaulter base
were true.
9:
Getting caught here'd be a recipe
for disaster. Let's get this over with.
14:
...Strange. I thought there were
supposed to be Updaters taken
prisoner here?
17:
Maybe the lead about all those
disappearances was just wrong?
25:
I don't like the look of this... What's
our next move?
29:
Let's go check it out. They might be
asking for help.
34:
So there was someone here! Hold
on, we'll call for backup—
39:
Bah!
Your concern is most unneeded!
48:
The strength of entire armies dwells
within my sword—the
hyper-oscillating Zantetsu Blade!
53:
H-huh? Wait a minute, with powers
like that, how did you even get
caught in the first place?
56:
The Updater has escaped! Deploy
security squads immediately!
58:
You're surrounded. Lay down your
weapons at once and—
66:
Behold the technique of the mecha
ninja samurai—the Moonslash of the
Mists!
70: Th-that was a bit overkill, wasn't it?
79:
Alert! Emergency underway!
Do NOT let the prisoner escape!
82: Crap. What do we do now?
86:
Every word of deliberation is breath
wasted—we shall cut our way
through. Trust in my blade!
93:
Hah-hah! And with that, our enemy
fades from sight. A victory earned
with ease.
97:
Uh-huh... Would you mind explaining
what just happened? Why did you
get yourself captured intentionally?
101:
Hah-hah! I was but investigating the
Updater disappearances, same as
you. Getting captured merely
expedited the process.
105:
You will be pleased to hear that 
I rescued the poor abducted souls
prior to your arrival, Lord Alk.
110:
Wait. Why the hell do you know his
name?
114:
Whatever do you mean, Lord
Nimbus? That is but trivial
information to one as
knowledgeable as me.
118:
Indeed, the truth is clear as
day—you are wayfarers from a
distant world!
123:
And what exactly is your endgame
here?
127:
A prudent question—one which will
be answered promptly!
131:
My true name is Code Cracker,
though the people know me by
another name—ZANTETSU, ninja
samurai and warrior of justice.
133:
I have but one singular objective: to
embark on a journey with you!
138:
All that just for an off-world
vacation? Seriously?
143:
You are the heroes who laid low the
Administrator and saved our world! 
I wish to join your ranks and be a
wandering warrior!
148: You knew about that too, huh...
153:
I trust that serves as ample proof of
the vast extent of my abilities? Well?
Does it?!
157:
I, uh... I mean...
Nimbus, what do you think?
162:
A robot ninja samurai... Smells awful
suspicious to me, but whatever. You
decide.
167:
I see it writ plain in your eyes—you
harbor doubt. In that case, I have no
choice but to use my trump card...
174:
Please take me! Please take me!
Please take me! PLEASE, PLEASE! I BEG
YOU, PLEASE TAKE ME WITH YOU!
180:
Y-you don't need to have to throw
yourself at my feet like that!
Stop bowing!
184:
This is the perfect chance to realize
my only dream—and to pen the next
chapter in the swashbuckling epic
of this humble ninja samurai!
188:
In the name of all that is good and
honorable in this world, I beg of you!
HAVE MERCY ON THIS BUNDLE OF
METAL AND CODE!
194:
A village suspended in the air... And...
are those worlds? A scene that
beggars belief!
196:
At long last, I have arrived... to a
world just like that of the motion
pictures I adore!
200:
Wh-what?! Lord Alk!
Could it be... Are there real samurai
and ninja among your ranks?!
203:
Uh, y-yeah. We've got a couple of
those, sure.
208:
To think the day would come when 
I could behold a TRUE ninja or
samurai... Be still, my whirring
processor!
212:
Where did you even hear about
samurai and ninja, Zantetsu?
216:
From movies, of course! And
manga.
...And anime.
219: O-oh. Well, that's cool, I guess.
223:
Do not misunderstand! I am no
mere HOBBYIST. I have studied the
blade rigorously, all to become the
best ninja samurai there ever was!
227:
And... my work is a matter of
historical preservation! I wished to...
recover data previously lost in the
inferno that engulfed our world.
231:
First, I must make haste to your
library! No, perhaps an interview
with a real-life ninja or samurai is in
order first?
233:
Or mayhap an excursion? This is a
once-in-a-lifetime chance to see
the world to which I have devoted
every fiber of my being!
237:
Starting to regret bringing this one
along yet?
242:
Erm... Well, at least he'll keep us on
our toes.
247:
It is done! My decision has been
made. Lords Alk and Nimbus—pray
accompany me!
